✨HINT✨ Do you hate part of your process? 🫣
It’s normal. We can’t love every part of what we do but I have some ideas that might help! 🙌🏻

1. Get the right tools! I used to hate rolling these flowers out. It was tedious time consuming work as each one I had to hold in my hand but getting this foam hat has saved me so much time and doesn’t heat up my clay. 

2. Slow down. Give yourself a longer timeline to finish. Slowing down will help you focus on the moment and not the pressure of finishing. 

3. Do less!! Don’t try and get so much done at once. Mix it up and do different things between each process point so you don’t get bored. 

4. Hate it 🤣 it’s really ok to not like a part of the process. As long as it’s worth it in the end! 

Follow for more tips 😂🤣 (that’s what I’m suppose to say right?)

#polymerclay #smallbusinesssupport #creativeprocess

BUT 🛑 !! I’m TRYING 👏🏻 TO 👏🏻 STOP 👏🏻
I’m trying to break the cycle! Instead of starting one thing before I finish another I start multiple things at the same time and then I finish one all the way through and then move onto the next one. And so it’s basically the same things I’ve been doing but different.

🫣😬 That was really hard to admit.

⁉️What’s your favorite part?!

I have so many favorite parts of making an earring but to see all of my other favorite parts come together is my favorite part.

✨HOT TIP✨ 
Make what makes you happy! 
My question though is, do you? Is it easy?

I’m generally not a people pleaser in the traditional sense but when it comes to creating, making, art, I can get caught up in the desire for external validation and then I hyper fixate on creating to make other people happy and in return I burn myself out. 

Now, there is nothing wrong with creating for others. Their is something so rewarding bringing people joy through your craft but you shouldn’t do it to the detriment of yourself!

What is it that you create that brings you joy!

💥 UNPOPULAR OPINION 💥
If you can do what I can do, do it.
If you think you can do it better, I hope you do!
If you are just learning, as me, I don’t keep secrets. 

Where would I go to find growth, innovation, and increased creativity if there weren’t people pushing me to be better by doing what I do but better? 

For those who straight up copy me, idc. I hope you take what you learned and create something new with it and if you don’t, I will. That’s the beauty. Creativity is endless, creation is only limited by thought. Don’t stop creating.

✨ASMR✨
I love the sounds of clicking and clacking. 
I abhor the wet whispers and eating. 
What about you?

I hope, if nothing else, my girls learn that they are brave, bold, and they don’t have to be anyone but themselves. 

Here’s what I do to show them their capable of doing hard things:
⭐️ I show them that it’s hard and I do it anyway. 
⭐️ I encourage them to create 
⭐️ I give them opportunities to learn new crafts

🐆Cheetah Facts:
✨ Females are badass single moms. They live in solitude unless they are raising their cubs and then it’s just them and their cubs got 16-24 months

✨ They’re not the average athlete. They only drink water every 3-4 days and they are still the fastest land animal.

✨Males are eternal frat boys. They only lives in groups with other males. No girls allowed. 

✨They cry, but for their prey. The lines on their face are called tear lines and it’s said to help with with deflecting the sun and seeing long distances.
 
✨They’re a lover not a fighter. They aren’t aggressive, they avoid larger prey and will walk away instead of staying to fight. 

✨ They’re singers. They don’t roar, they chirp like birds.

Allow yourself to winter. Allow yourself to be bored. Allow yourself to have creative blocks. Allow yourself to create shorty art because you don’t know what to create. I promise if you allow yourself these things but never stop doing creative things or bare minimum never stop thinking about creative things, you’ll be ok. Your winter will turn into spring and you will bloom. You will thrive. 

I wintered for over a year. It feels like I’m returning to a garden overrun with weeds, filled with things that are planted that no one will eat. In the beginning it felt overwhelming. I weeded, I removed plants, I rebuilt my garden. Now I have to tend to it, I have to wait to see how it will grow. It’s scary to think all my hard work might not be fruitful but if running a small business is anything like gardening (which I’m starting to think it is) it will be worth it. I might not get a five star for my tomatoes but I know I’ll enjoy them in my salad with others who may just enjoy tomatoes in their salads too and to me, knowing just a few will be touched by what I produce is worth it.

I woke up this morning with some heavy feelings. 
Sometimes I put too much pressure on myself.
I want to give so much of myself that I get overwhelmed with the expectation I set then I start to overthink. And overfeel. 

The thing is, 
You don’t have to be the best at what you do. 
You don’t have to be friends with all the other moms.
You don’t have to be liked by all of Instagram. 
You don’t have to be involved in every school event.
You don’t have to be releasing new designs every week. 

You just have to be happy being you. 
You have to be satisfied with your effort. You’re best effort can never be compared to someone else’s. Hell, you can’t even compare your todays best to your yesterdays best. 

Here’s to being mediocre with a few prodigy days sprinkled in there.

“That doesn’t mean that every idea that you come up with is going to be genius, but if there is something that you feel is good, something that you want to do, something that means something to you, try to do it.” -Stan Lee

Don’t wait to create! 
Just do it. And do it your way. It’ll be the best way! 
Make shitty art till it’s good and then great. 

If you focus on what you’re doing and how you’re doing it and how you want it to be done and you challenge yourself to do your best there will be no room to compare yourself to what other people are doing, how they are doing or comparing yourself to their best. Their best is not comparable to yours.

I couldn’t even wear earrings. 🫣
I just didn’t want to be seen. 
I was so anxious and depressed and hated who I was, how I looked, how I felt. I lost a lot of people in my life and I felt like I just was never good enough. I tried to be someone people liked. I tried to be what people needed. 

I slowly started taking back control. This last year I did a lot of self reflection and I’m grateful for the years that led up to it. Because without the hard days I wouldn’t know how to bloom. I’m finally living authentically. I finally found me. 

I’m now able to create without anything holding me back. I’m not creating for anyone or anything other than the expression of self and the desire to help others feel more free to express to the world who they are. 

Since the beginning of Lyss Made This I used the phrase, Be Bold, Be Brave, Be you. It’s a phrase that always resonated but I never felt like I could truly stand behind it because I didn’t truly know how to do it myself but now I can because I’ve finally found my way. 

So if you take anything from this message, take this: 
You are bravest enough to be bold and you’re bold enough to be you. Step into it, it’s not as scary as it seems.

This isn’t what I wanted to do today. Actually the last week didn’t even go how I hoped. I didn’t post content I didn’t share to stories. I mixed colors and organized my animals and made my files for the small animal studs but I didn’t get much further because I’m still learning balance and I’m teaching myself how to give myself grace.

Running a small business isn’t easy especially in the day of social media with the constant comparison of others easily don’t through the onslaught of images and videos daily delivered to your feed. 

Imposter syndrome has been creeping in, fitting for the spooky season. I keep losing more followers than I’m gaining and my engagement is doing so badly that I’ve found myself throwing a few imposter parties. But the best thing I do is remind myself why I’m doing what I’m doing and then I stand up and take a breath and keep moving forward.

Don’t stop doing what you love because an app on your phone isn’t giving you validation. Keep doing what you love because you love it. And the more love we share with others the more love people will feel.

Now, this post might not be for everyone. In fact it might cause some of you to leave and that’s ok. I want this space to be safe for everyone to be themselves. And since it is my space I want it to be safe for me to share… me. 

To many this earring might mean nothing. But for me it’s in honor of my faith transition. A reminder to live my authentic self. To think about my life here and now. To live my life full of love, and kindness, and joy. 

I want to create relationships with my family and friends with so much authenticity and love and intention to enjoy every ounce of them now in this life. To know them and to honor them as they are in their present space. I don’t want to live a life on earth to try and achieve an eternal afterlife that potentially  wouldn’t even include my loved ones. 

I don’t know for sure where we go after we pass on from this life. But I do know we shouldn’t waste the time we have here not loving the people who have been placed in our lives because of their differing beliefs for an afterlife with a God who believes you can’t be with your family forever if your family isn’t worthy to be in the same heaven as you. 

So I choose to Think Telestial, to shoot for the stars.

Tell me here 👇🏻
As an artist, what is your hope?

What’s it going to hurt?!

You owe it to yourself to become everything you’ve dreamed of becoming. 

Here’s How:

✨Shed yourself of misplaced expectations. 
✨Rid yourself of fear. 
✨Remove all self-doubting energy. 
✨Learn patience.
✨Take action. 
✨Allow growth. 
✨Prepare to pivot. 
✨Don’t limit your dreams. 

What’s your Big Dream?!

Why I keep posting every day even if I don’t sell a single earring or make a dime. 

1. I just want to make beautiful things even if nobody cares. I think creating good and beautiful things will eventually be rewarded. Patience is being learned. 

2. Creative minds inspire others. Sharing my creativity and my process will show others they too can create. And creating is the ultimate way to connect with oneself. The more we can connect with ourselves the more we know and the more we can give. 

3. Simply because I can. And a lot because I need to create. There are no rules to creativity. Just do what makes you happy and share that happiness with others. Lose your fear.

✨HERE is my secret 👇🏻👇🏻

How to be more creative:

1. Recognize that you are already a creative creature. Start noticing the ways you were creative today. Write them down. Tell me here to share with others. But acknowledging your creativity is the key to allowing it to grow. Like anything we have to honor, love, and nurture for it to grow. 

Which transitions perfectly into …
2. Don’t diminish or belittle your creativity. Your creativity needs to be seen like a growing living thing. If you want it to grow up big and strong don’t call it names, bullying its efforts. Your creativity can be sensitive in the beginning give it encouragement.

3. Use it. Let it shine. Allow it to be silly and weird and ugly. Let it fail so you can encourage it to get up and keep going. This is the part where you let actions speak louder than your words. Don’t fear using your creativity. It won’t look the same as anyone else and that’s the point. It was born from a different person with different circumstances and different upbringing and that’s what makes your creativity so unique. 

❤️

⁉️What’s something you’re holding off doing because you’re worried you won’t get it right?!

Today I created for me and for my family. I was so nervous to start this recipe book. I sat on the supplies for days and before that they sat in the cart for weeks. I didn’t think I’d do it justice that I’d mess it up, that it wouldn’t be “perfect” to my standards. 

And guess what? I did mess up and it’s not perfect ( I still need to erase the pencil marks) but when I finished this page, I cried. I was filled with relief that I accomplished something that seemed so scary and that I actually love it and am so excited to fill this book with the recipes that are tried and true and that my family loves. 

Don’t hold yourself back from creating, no matter how scared you are!

Just do some shit. It’s all you have to do is just do it. 

Once you start a whole new world will be unlocked. Possibly filled with imposter syndrome and comparison 😅 but there is also joy and satisfaction from creating that really out weigh the negative. 

And soon I’ll be revisiting old ideas and creating something new and I’m so excited about it. One of them being those shaker earrings. Any guesses? Anything you’d like to see?! Let me know!

Living in the moment is a skill that has to be practiced everyday but it’s worth it when I do it right. It’s worth it to accept your self in the depths of unknowing who you are and where you’re going because as you accept that process of self improvement you’ll find your self worth in every stage. No matter where you’re headed or who you’ll become your worthy of all great things now, in this exact moment.

It’s just. Really satisfying.

I hosted my very first POTluck to kick off the new year. I first threw the idea out there to see what friends would be interested and then I was committed to making it happen.

I had previously made cookies and brownies with 🍃butter that I didn’t infuse myself. I had no idea the dosing I just went for it, living on the side of caution. Every product however, you could taste the 🍃 not much but it was there some stronger than others. I first made brownies, then sugar cookies with frosting, swig style, all green. I then made puppy chow and blondies. Some are still in our freezer 😉

I was sweeted out and so I tried a seasoned pretzel with oil I had infused and I still didn’t know dosing per serving but I knew how strong the oil was at least and I have a live in taste tester to tell me the effects. I am not one to “wait and see” on things like this but he is. 

I wanted to know exactly how much 🍃 was going into my items and how much mg each serving was so I could know exactly what I was getting in my food and the POTluck was the challenge I needed. 

I took a whole month meal planning and researching and like my true procrastinating self it didn’t all come together till the week before. I also found an appreciation for that high school math I never thought I’d use. In the end I knew the doses of everything. 
This is what I made:
💨Pineapple and Sage Gimlet w/ tincture if desired. 
1mg per dropper
💨Chimichurri Steak and Burrata Crostini
5mg per 1 tbsp of chimichurri
💨Shaved Fennel Salad
1mg per 1 tbsp of vinaigrette 
💨Butter and Prosecco Poached Shrimp over Risotto
8mg per serving
💨 Pavlova with Vanilla Ice Cream, Berry Compote, and candied kumquats. Infused whipped cream and white chocolate magic shell. 
2.5 mg per 1 tbsp of whipped cream
2.5 mg per 1 tbsp of magic shell. 

It was the most chill event I ever hosted. The food turned out amazing and everyone was able to dose themselves making sure I had options for those who don’t partake in 🍃 to those who do regularly. It was the most joy I’ve felt in a long time making food for others and I can’t wait to do it again.
